From: i915-rt-audit
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/display: recover instead of wedging on lost flip_done

On PREEMPT_RT the vblank-evasion critical section runs preemptible by
design (the RT series removes the local_irq_disable() because
dev->event_lock - a sleeping rtmutex on RT - must be taken inside it,
intel_crtc.c:574/593/740 vs :637/:650). The resulting races are accepted
and logged ("Atomic update failure on pipe ..."), but a flip whose
completion is lost currently wedges the pipe permanently:

  - the undelivered drm_pending_vblank_event pins the CRTC vblank
    refcount (drm_vblank.c: vblank_disable_fn requires refcount == 0),
  - so the disable/re-enable cycle that would rewrite the DE pipe IMR
    never runs again (drm_vblank_get on later commits only increments
    the refcount once enabled),
  - so every subsequent commit times out 10 s in wait_for_flip_done,
    the compositor freezes, and only a modeset or reboot recovers.

Observed in the field as a full desktop freeze during video-call load,
with "flip_done timed out" followed by a minute of compositor pageflip
timeouts until power-off.

Make the failure degrade to a dropped frame instead: after
drm_atomic_helper_wait_for_flip_done(), any commit whose flip_done still
has not completed gets recovered - deliver the stranded i915-private
async-flip event, cycle the vblank irq off/on (drm_crtc_vblank_off
flushes pending core events and drops their vblank references;
drm_crtc_vblank_on re-enables and rewrites the pipe interrupt mask),
and force-complete the commit so cleanup proceeds.

This does not fix the underlying RT race - it removes its ability to
take the session down. The drm_err line doubles as a diagnostic: a
single occurrence means recovery worked; one occurrence per commit
means interrupt delivery is dead above the device level (masked
oneshot MSI line / wedged irq thread) and the problem is outside the
display engine.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_display.c
@@ -7531,6 +7531,43 @@
 	 */
 	drm_atomic_helper_wait_for_flip_done(display->drm, &state->base);
 
+	/*
+	 * A flip_done that never arrives must not wedge the pipe forever:
+	 * an undelivered event pins the vblank refcount, which blocks the
+	 * disable/re-enable cycle that would rewrite the interrupt mask,
+	 * so a dead flip self-locks (observed on PREEMPT_RT, where the
+	 * vblank evasion races by design). Flush stranded events, cycle
+	 * the vblank irq, and force-complete the commit so this degrades
+	 * to a dropped frame instead of a frozen display.
+	 */
+	for_each_new_intel_crtc_in_state(state, crtc, new_crtc_state, i) {
+		struct drm_crtc_commit *commit = new_crtc_state->uapi.commit;
+
+		if (!commit || !new_crtc_state->hw.active)
+			continue;
+
+		if (try_wait_for_completion(&commit->flip_done))
+			continue;
+
+		drm_err(display->drm,
+			"[CRTC:%d:%s] flip_done lost, recovering vblank/flip delivery\n",
+			crtc->base.base.id, crtc->base.name);
+
+		spin_lock_irq(&display->drm->event_lock);
+		if (crtc->flip_done_event) {
+			drm_crtc_send_vblank_event(&crtc->base,
+						   crtc->flip_done_event);
+			crtc->flip_done_event = NULL;
+		}
+		spin_unlock_irq(&display->drm->event_lock);
+
+		intel_crtc_vblank_off(new_crtc_state);
+		intel_crtc_vblank_on(new_crtc_state);
+
+		if (!try_wait_for_completion(&commit->flip_done))
+			complete_all(&commit->flip_done);
+	}
+
 	for_each_new_intel_crtc_in_state(state, crtc, new_crtc_state, i) {
 		if (new_crtc_state->do_async_flip)
 			intel_crtc_disable_flip_done(state, crtc);
